One Azure specific thing to bear in mind is that Dynamic IP Addresses aren't assigned until the VM is booted - as such you may need to use a Data Source to obtain that value once the VM is booted (e.g. the azurerm_public_ip Data Source, with a relevant example here) - and then call the Provisioner from a separate block (e.g. a null_resource) like below:

